author: lundblad
msg: Plug, using chewing gum of my favorite taste, a major and a minor memory
leak in svn switch --relocate.
NOTE: This commit contains an unrelated change that was reverted in r19536.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/relocate.c
(relocate_entry): Don't allocate the new URL fields in the access baton's
pool, because svn_wc__modify_entry will duplicate them there.
While here, use apr_pstrcat instead of apr_psprintf.  (This is the minor
leak).
(svn_wc_relocate2): Use a subpool for iteration.  This was The Leak(TM).
